At least 25 people died in a road accident at Kambuu, Kibwezi sub-county, Makueni on Tuesday. Area OCPD Leonard Kimaiyo said the accident involved a bus and a center transporting vegetable oil.The bus, which was on its way to Nairobi from Mombasa, collided with the tanker killing the 25 instantly.The injured were rushed to Makindu sub-county hospital. Police said the driver of the bus was overtaking at Kalulu bridge when he collided with the trailer.The truck driver and the turn boy were seriously injured.